The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Nov. 17: The rate of inflation rose to 5.30 per cent for the week ended November 4 from 5.09 per cent in the previous week mainly due to increase in the prices of food and manufactured items. The wholesale price-based inflation stood at 4.04 per cent during the corresponding week last year. The wholesale price index (WPI) for all commodities rose 0.2 per cent to 208.8 points.

 Guwahati, Nov. 17: The Assam government today constituted a committee to examine all aspects of revision of minimum wages in the tea industry. The committee will hold an enquiry and advise the government in the matter.

 Mumbai, Nov. 17: Pantaloon Retail India will invest up to Rs 17.50 crore to set up a subsidiary for office supplies business, the company informed the Bombay Stock Exchange.

 Mumbai, Nov. 17: Mangalore Refinery and Petrochemicals (MRPL) will receive Rs 142.88 crore as public sector oil marketing companies such as IOC, HPC and BPC have agreed to refund discounts extended by the company on domestic LPG and kerosene sold under the public distribution system.

 Mumbai, Nov. 17: Videocon Industriess global subsidiary has entered into a production sharing contract with Timor Sea Designated Authority to complete works related to oil-drilling.




